    "ideation": "The baby chick animation captures the frantic, adorable energy of a newly hatched bird. The performance centers on the 'peep-peep' vocalization and the hyper-fixated, wide-eyed innocence characteristic of a chick. I used sharp, sudden eye-widening and gaze shifts to simulate bird-like scanning. The mouth wave is treated as the beak: it snaps from a wide, chirping amplitude to a tiny, compressed line. The color palette utilizes warm yellows and bright oranges, suggesting soft down feathers and a tiny beak. The motion arc is: resting, startled peep, rapid chirping, and then settling back into a curious, head-tilting observation.",
